    {
      "content": "A PubMed query regarding the role of Interleukin-23 (IL-23) in the modulation of the Th17 cell pathway in rheumatoid arthritis identified multiple peer-reviewed articles (e.g., PMID: 28143887, 29444913) describing how IL-23 drives Th17 cell differentiation via STAT3 signaling and promotes autoimmune responses. These papers also link IL-23-induced Th17 activity to the secretion of RANKL and pro-inflammatory cytokines that contribute to bone erosion.",
      "justification": "We needed external, validated evidence of IL-23’s impact on Th17 cells and downstream bone-remodeling processes in RA.",
      "source_id": "PubMed-IL23-Th17"
    },
    {
      "content": "A broad Europe PMC literature search on matrix metalloproteinases (MMPs) in rheumatoid arthritis showed consistent findings that MMPs degrade extracellular matrix components and are upregulated by fibroblast-like synoviocytes (FLS) in inflamed joints (for instance, PMID: 32554467, PMC: 7486040). Several reviews emphasize that MMP-driven cartilage and bone tissue damage are hallmarks of chronic RA pathology, linking MMP activity to osteoclast differentiation and bone resorption.",
      "justification": "We sought confirmation from a comprehensive source on how MMP-driven extracellular matrix remodeling contributes to joint damage and indirectly affects bone integrity.",
      "source_id": "EuropePMC-MMPs-RA"
