      "content": "A subsequent PubMed query on Denosumab in rheumatoid arthritis (e.g., PMID: 32348381) highlighted clinical evidence that this anti-RANKL therapy reduces both osteoclastogenesis and bone erosions, leading to improved bone mineral density (BMD). Additional publications also suggest a secondary effect on pro-inflammatory pathways, including potential downregulation of MMP-9 in osteoclast precursors, though findings remain under investigation.",
